{"type":"message","id":"2bb311b7","parentId":"54dad025","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:20:16.666Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `Editor.log` was updated at 10:56 today (June 9) - that's about when the sub-agent would have been running. So Unity DID start up, but the `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` wasn't updated - meaning the pipeline ran but the log was written to a different location, or it ran but the `-logFile` parameter wasn't used properly, or... \n\nWait, `Editor.log` is 0 bytes - it's empty. That means either:\n1. Unity started and immediately crashed without writing anything\n2. Or Unity was already running and the log was truncated\n\nBut actually, if sub-agent ran the bat file which launched Unity with `-logFile \"%LOG_FILE%\"`, then Unity would write the log to `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`, not `Editor.log`. But `Editor.log` is also 0 bytes which is odd.\n\nLet me check what happened at 10:56 when Unity supposedly ran. The `Editor.log` being 0 bytes might indicate that Unity was launched with `-logFile` pointing elsewhere. But `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` wasn't updated either...\n\nActually, hold on. Looking more carefully: the `Editor.log` has `LastWriteTime 2026/6/9 10:56:02` and is 0 bytes. This is the Editor log which Unity writes to normally. When Unity runs with `-batchmode -quit -logFile`, it writes to that logFile. But the Editor.log being updated at 10:56 suggests Unity WAS active at that time.\n\nThe key question is: why didn't the bat file update `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`?\n\nThere could be an issue where the sub-agent said it executed the bat but the exec command might not have worked properly on Windows. The sub-agent was told to run `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat` - and the TOOLS.md specifically says \"exec 工具会直接启动 bat\" - but maybe something went wrong with the sub-agent's execution.\n\nActually, the problem might be simpler: the sub-agent checked the Unity exit code and scanned the log, but the log had an old timestamp. The sub-agent might have been checking the wrong file or the log check ran while Unity was still writing.\n\nIn any case, the result is clear: the sub-agent's Unity execution didn't produce a new log file, and the hot update pipeline wasn't actually run.\n\nLet me see if the sub-agent's exec actually ran successfully or not. Let me check the sub-agent's transcript.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EcYNHzYuAH0A9nI9SAPe9888","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:75fa877a-52b8-45dc-bea5-d7d8f554ffd4","includeTools":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":163,"output":641,"cacheRead":34816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35620,"cost":{"input":0.000022820000000000002,"output":0.00017948,"cacheRead":0.000974848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001177148}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780975209591,"responseId":"9f236ee7-2c55-4c50-9135-8114f7fedf4c"}}
