{"type":"message","id":"948bc6c6","parentId":"40c52837","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:20:42.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `Editor.log` contains output from today (2026/6/9 11:12:29) showing the hot update pipeline DID run:\n\n1. `[Feishu] 发送结果 {\"StatusCode\":0,\"StatusMessage\":\"success\",\"code\":0,\"data\":{},\"msg\":\"success\"}` - It sent a Feishu notification\n2. `2026/6/9 11:12:29:end 'Excute Pipline:上传CDN',Consuming time:3.4844572s` - It completed the CDN upload step\n3. `本地测试环境已准备就绪` / `版本: 1.0.41` / `渠道: Test1` / `平台: Android` - All the hot update steps ran\n\nSo the Unity pipeline DID run! But the log was written to `Editor.log` instead of `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`.\n\nWait, that doesn't make sense. The bat file specifically uses `-logFile \"%LOG_FILE%\"` which should be `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`. But the Editor.log shows the pipeline output...\n\nOh wait - I see the issue now. The `Editor.log` timestamp shows **11:12** today, but the bat file uses `-logFile` to redirect to `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`. But then why is output in `Editor.log`?\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the timestamps:\n- `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` last write: `2026/6/4 11:56:09`\n- `Editor.log` last write: `2026/6/9 10:56:02` (0 bytes... wait it was 0 bytes earlier but now it has content?)\n\nWait, let me re-check. Earlier the output said `Editor.log` is 0 bytes. But now when I cat it, it has lots of content...\n\nActually no, the `Get-ChildItem` showed `Length 0` for `Editor.log`, but the `Get-Content` shows a lot of content. That's because PowerShell's `Get-ChildItem` can report size differently from actual content, or the file was being written to at that exact moment.\n\nActually, I think the issue is simpler: the `Editor.log` is Unity's default log location. When Unity runs with `-logFile`, it writes to the specified file AND the Editor.log. Or... Unity 2020.3 might only use the Editor.log as the main log regardless of `-logFile`.\n\nActually no. When you pass `-logFile` to Unity, it should redirect ALL output to that file. But wait - maybe the bat was NOT actually executed by the sub-agent. Maybe the sub-agent ran the git steps and then tried to run the bat but Unity was already running (because you had opened it earlier?), so the bat couldn't create a new session.\n\nBut then where did the Editor.log content from 11:12 come from?\n\nOh! I think I understand now. When主人 said \"我自己手动执行了\" - he manually ran the pipeline AFTER the sub-agent tried. So the Editor.log content at 11:12 is from his manual run, not the sub-agent's run.\n\nSo the timeline is:\n1. sub-agent runs bat → Unity launched, wrote to `-logFile` but maybe the log went to `Editor.log` or the bat didn't actually execute the Unity command properly\n2. Or: sub-agent's Unity execution happened, wrote 10:56 timestamp to Editor.log (0 bytes at that time)\n3. 主人手动执行 at ~11:12 → pipeline ran, wrote to Editor.log\n\nThe fact that `Editor.log` shows \"2026/6/9 11:12:29\" pipeline output confirms the manual run worked.\n\nNow the question is: why didn't `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` get updated by the sub-agent's run? \n\nPossible reason: the sub-agent ran `taskkill /f /im Unity.exe` which killed ALL Unity processes, including any batchmode Unity that was running. But wait, the bat launches Unity in a new process... \n\nActually, the real problem might be simpler. Let me look at the sub-agent flow again:\n\nThe sub-agent:\n1. Kills Unity processes\n2. Runs git pull\n3. Runs bat → this launches Unity in batch mode\n4. Waits for Unity to exit\n5. Checks log\n\nBut what if step 2 (git pull) modified some script files, and when Unity loaded the project, the scripts were being compiled (which generates new assemblies), and then the `-executeMethod` was called before compilation finished? In that case, Unity might have exited with the script not found.\n\nBut actually, the bat uses `-batchmode -quit`, and Unity waits for scripts to compile before running `-executeMethod`.\n\nOR - a more likely scenario: the `Editor.log` was written to because the bat's `-logFile` parameter pointed to `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` but the file was locked by a previous Unity process (from 6月4日), so Unity fell back to writing to `Editor.log`. And the sub-agent checked `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` which was stale, found no errors, and declared success.\n\nActually, I realize now that the key finding is:\n\n1. `Editor.log` has content from today (11:12) showing the pipeline ran successfully - but this was主人的 manual run\n2. `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` is from 6/4 - the sub-agent's run didn't touch it\n\nBut wait, when Unity uses `-logFile`, it OVERWRITES the file, so even if it was locked, it should have been overwritten... unless Unity had a crash during launch.\n\nHmm, but the `Editor.log` is 0 bytes when I checked with `Get-ChildItem`... Let me look again.\n\nActually, `Get-ChildItem` showed `Length 0` for `Editor.log` but `Get-Content -Tail 200` showed lots of content. That's puzzling. Maybe the file was truncated/recreated between the two commands.\n\nAnyway, the point is: the sub-agent's execution of the bat did not produce a new `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`, which means Unity didn't successfully run the pipeline during that batch mode session. The script's check of the log file was flawed because it checked a stale file.\n\nI should tell the主人 what I found and fix the sub-agent flow to:\n1. Check the log file's timestamp AFTER running Unity (not just scan for errors)\n2. Also check `Editor.log` for errors\n3. Log the Unity exit code properly\n\nLet me update the hot update documentation and the sub-agent task definition to add this check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到原因了！`Editor.log` 里确实有今天的流水线日志，但时间是 **11:12**——那是你手动执行的结果。sub-agent 跑的 Unity batch 没有写入 `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log`。\n\n问题出在 sub-agent 的**检查逻辑有缺陷**：\n- 它跑完 bat 后去扫 `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` 的**内容**，没发现错误就认为成功了\n- 但实际上 Unity batch 进程可能因为某些原因（License、编译等）**没真正走到流水线步骤**，也没往日志里写\n- 日志文件还是 **6月4日** 的旧内容，检查结果自然假阳性\n\n我来修复这个 bug——加上**日志时间戳校验**："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9zRiqf9PlSTpmK9z2iCt1482","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TOOLS.md","offset":1,"limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":5407,"output":1684,"cacheRead":36224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43315,"cost":{"input":0.0007569800000000001,"output":0.00047152,"cacheRead":0.0010142719999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0022427719999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780975225429,"responseId":"5828de52-e19c-4956-b379-ac4e15b20e9d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d798a7ce","parentId":"948bc6c6","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:20:42.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_9zRiqf9PlSTpmK9z2iCt1482","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n\n[178 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780975242763}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ed959af","parentId":"d798a7ce","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:20:48.781Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me update the TOOLS.md to add the timestamp check in the hot update process.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_s5eDrvWU2bXBT7IofP2L0395","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TOOLS.md","edits":[{"oldText":"**编译失败检测逻辑：**\n- ⚠️ **Unity 退出码为 0 不代表流水线完全成功！** 流水线内部步骤可能失败（如 git pull），但 Unity 仍以 0 退出\n- 必须额外扫描日志文件，检测以下致命错误：\n  - `error CS\\d+:` — C# 编译报错（硬错误）\n  - `git更新失败` — 流水线内 git pull 失败\n  - `Build completed with.*errors` — Unity 构建统计有 errors\n- 检查命令：`powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern 'error CS\\d+:|git更新失败|Build completed with'\"`\n- 匹配到关键字 → **视为失败**，发失败通知（hotupdate-fail）\n- 无匹配 + Unity 退出码 0 → **视为成功**，发成功通知（hotupdate-ok）","newText":"**编译结果检测逻辑（两步校验）：**\n\n**第一步：检查日志是否已更新（防假阳性）**\n- ⚠️ **Unity 退出码为 0 不代表流水线真正跑了！** 可能 Unity 进程异常退出但 exit code 还是 0\n- 在运行 bat 前先记录 `BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log` 的 LastWriteTime\n- bat 执行完后，重新检查该文件的 LastWriteTime\n- **如果时间没有变化 → 流水线没有实际执行，视为失败**\n- 同时检查 `Editor.log`（`%USERPROFILE%/AppData/Local/Unity/Editor/Editor.log`）是否有本次运行的线索\n\n**第二步：扫描日志内容（防部分失败）**\n如果日志时间戳已更新，扫描检测以下致命错误：\n  - `error CS\\d+:` — C# 编译报错（硬错误）\n  - `git更新失败` — 流水线内 git pull 失败\n  - `Build completed with.*errors` — Unity 构建统计有 errors\n- 检查命令：`powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern 'error CS\\d+:|git更新失败|Build completed with'\"`\n- 匹配到关键字 → **视为失败**，发失败通知（hotupdate-fail）\n- 时间戳未更新 → **视为失败**（流水线未执行），发失败通知\n- 时间戳已更新 + 无关键字匹配 + Unity 退出码 0 → **视为成功**，发成功通知（hotupdate-ok）","matchCount":"1"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":230,"output":728,"cacheRead":43264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44222,"cost":{"input":0.000032200000000000003,"output":0.00020384000000000003,"cacheRead":0.001211392,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001447432}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780975242764,"responseId":"c5fd141f-0e29-41e6-aaad-f4c276ff7c67"}}
